      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for CFD simulation must be under formal configuration control with documented verification tests, traceability to requirements, and a validated release process consistent with MRL 5 requirements (Level 4).",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is a commercially validated package with documented version control and standard regression test suites. Release notes and patch logs are maintained. Minor gaps exist in formal traceability documentation between solver sub-modules and individual hemolysis model requirements, but overall software quality practices are consistent with engineering best practice for cardiovascular device simulation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical code verification must demonstrate correctness of solver implementation through method of manufactured solutions or equivalent formal verification at Level 4.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the Navier-Stokes solver confirms second-order spatial convergence. Hemolysis transport scalar verified against analytical benchmark for simple shear flow. Code verification is complete and meets Level 4 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Discretization error must be quantified via systematic mesh refinement study with Richardson extrapolation or equivalent, achieving Grid Convergence Index below 5% on hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. Richardson extrapolation applied to hemolysis index; GCI of 3.8% achieved on the primary QoI. Discretization error is within the required threshold."
