      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis damage model form must be justified through systematic comparison of multiple candidate constitutive models against experimental data, with uncertainty in model form quantified at Level 5.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) was selected based on its widespread use in published CFD hemolysis studies and demonstrated agreement with FDA pump benchmark data. Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to model-form assumptions was examined qualitatively. While a formal multi-model comparison with quantified model-form uncertainty was not completed, the selected model is well-established in the literature and its limitations are broadly understood within the cardiovascular device modelling community."
    },
