      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test samples must be characterised with sufficient donor diversity and sample size to support statistical comparison with model predictions at Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were obtained from the FDA benchmark dataset, which employed a standardised bovine blood protocol across multiple laboratories. Inter-laboratory variability is documented. The dataset represents a well-accepted reference standard in the cardiovascular device modelling community, and the sample size is considered adequate for benchmark purposes given the consistency of results across participating laboratories."
